y = c_1e^{kx}+c_2e^{-kx}
\lambda = -\mu^2
y(x) = A e^{\mu x} + B e^{-\mu x}
y(0)=0 \implies A+B=0
y'\left( \frac{\pi}{2}\right) = 0 \implies 2 A \sinh{\left(\mu \frac{\pi}{2}\right)} =0 
